reviews.text: relaxing place to enjoy coffee, local beer and other drinks. there is a very open view from the restaurant. staffs are quite friendly. however the    sign for the restaurant is not so obvious when we came out from the lift. suggested restaurant can give some indications if possible.

A secret garden for teachers or members of education to take a deep breath from hard work after hours of teaching. There are two seminar rooms for staff training or simply a sharing of interests. A very nice place for dining out and fireworks appreciation definitely.

Nice service. I would say the best service. Manager is very friendly, provide me and my girl friend with free dessert and fruit. Environment is the best and there is not much people coming making it even better!
I Feel that It is like my family. So good so sweet!

Great view, comfy, spacious and a great overall experience. Went there for dinner. Tried whole lot of different food, not that great, unless you enjoy fusion food, wouldn't recommend. It was a complete waste of a good rib-eye steak, the lamb is very gamey and the spaghetti was flavorless.
